remarks.para:
It is highly recommended to call  for returned image explicitly:

using (var colorImage = capture.ColorImage)
{
    if (colorImage != null)
    {
        // working with color image
    }
}

But  object automatically tracks all  objects it returned. And will call 
for all of them if client code didn't it.

It is highly recommended to call  for returned image explicitly:

using (var depthImage = capture.DepthImage)
{
    if (depthImage != null)
    {
        // working with depth image
    }
}

But  object automatically tracks all  objects it returned. And will call 
for all of them if client code didn't it.

It is highly recommended to call  for returned image explicitly:

